#Title      PMDNEO auditory tone ladder explicit lengths
#Composer   M.Koshikawa.
#Memo       one channel at a time, explicit note/rest lengths, no chord, no drum overlap

@001 000 005
 031 000 000 000 000 017 000 001 003 000
 031 000 000 000 000 025 000 002 003 000
 031 000 000 000 000 038 000 001 003 000
 004 018 000 015 002 000 000 001 003 000

; FM A/D are silent on YM2610 OPNB target
A ;silent
D ;silent

; FM active channels only: B/C/E/F
; Each part starts after explicit r1 blocks.
B t80 q8 o4 @0 c1 c1
C t80 q8 o4 @0 r1 r1 d1 d1
E t80 q8 o4 @0 r1 r1 r1 r1 e1 e1
F t80 q8 o4 @0 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 f1 f1

; SSG G/H/I: fixed volume, one channel at a time.
; Use long explicit notes. If SSG does not sustain, inspect mixer/volume/gate.
G t80 q8 V15 o4 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 g1 g1
H t80 q8 V15 o4 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 a1 a1
I t80 q8 V15 o4 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 r1 b1 b1

; Keep ADPCM-B off for this first auditory ladder.
J ;empty

; Keep rhythm / ADPCM-A off in this first ladder.
